title: The worst Hoarder on the Planet.

comments.comment: 10 years studying to never do the exam (or fail it and abandon the idea) and this house, it all paints a picture of anxiety, distress and depression

Your baby is so cuuuute, you're one of the few youtubers I've watched from childhood that hasn't either quit or had some terrible secret revealed about their past. So glad I still watch you. Hope all continues going well for you!
I had to clean a hoarder house before. Every time we cleaned it, we would come back, and it would look worse than last time. Idk how they managed to make it worse than it was before, but they did.
So cool to see father and son on screen together. Ken is a great dad to Felix

Just want to say that a horror game about guys trying to clean out a haunted house full of hoarded objects would be amazing on so many levels. Just the hoarding itself is enough to creep many people out. Throw some monsters or ghosts in there, make the story some kind of investigation into the hoarder's mysterious disappearance, add some creepy psychological elements, and you've got a full experience.
I want to cry for this woman. She seems so sweet, and it's so sad she was living like this. I hope she got the help she needs and is living better now. <3

As a former hoarder (still struggling ) i will say that depression is the main culprit here. when you lose the will to live, the will to socialize and get depended on retail therapy (buying stuff online) this happens. I believe I needed non-judgmental friends that time the most. Hoarders are extremely sensitive and they have a feeling of being left out. Been there, felt that.
Björn's already getting sponsorships at less than a year old. He's already looking to be a great successor.

Hording can be caused by many things. I had a great aunt that was very clean. But living during the depression then the wars where everyone gave for the war effort. Her garage was packed with extra stuff. Myself having lost everything twice in  my life has made it difficult to voluntarily get rid if items when downsizing. And that doesn't include many other ways people can become a horder.  I remember watching one of the horder episodes where a school teacher completly hid she was a horder. If you never seen inside her house you would never guess she lived like she did from her appearance in her public.  There are many different people you would never imagine that live like this.
my heart aches for her. i hope so so badly that she got the help that she needs and got to bake and cook for her family like she wanted to. god bless her. ️
Embarrassed to admit that the Bjorn bait worked miraculously, watched the entire sponsor up until he was put away
Pewds holding his baby to tempt us into watching the ad is definitely working
I feel a panic attack coming on thinking about having to clean a house like that. I feel very sorry for people who suffer from hoarding even though they can be really frustrating.

I hoard stuff due to ocd and trauma and tbh I see myself in these people and it makes me so sad, I’m on a much smaller scale because I’m lucky enough to have people in my life and opportunities to help get me out of my habits, but on any scale it’s so hard to deal with. I truly feel horrible for these people and what they must be going through to get this bad, I hope they find peace and happiness and are able to get help.
Normally these hoarders episodes are my favorite to watch ever, but this one hits wrong. The woman is clearly delusional and I hope she got help.
Wow, what a nice video

This happened to me too. I've lost almost ten years to studying. Once you've put in so much effort it's really hard to quit, even when you know you can't do it. It's hard to admit to other people as well, because you might be judged. You can never be honest to other people again, and be yourself around them.

One of my father’s coworkers is a horder. He had a heart attack a few years ago, so my father and some other coworkers got together to clean his house and property. The bathroom was the worst, the toilet was filled to the brim with piss and shid, so my father was in the basement trying to fix the water lines and while he was doing that he turn the water on to check if he fixed it, almost immediately he hears his coworkers screaming for him to turn it off so he did and ran upstairs. The water pressure was so strong that it blew all of the contents of the toilet all over the bathroom and his coworkers, everyone was gagging and running outside

I remember hearing a story about two brothers living in New York being hoarders for phone books, one of them died, when a pile of them fell on him, he was recovered many years later, when the other brother died and the apartment was torn down. I sometimes feel like when I have 2-3 pizza boxes I just haven't found the will to clean up, that it gets a little to much and throw it in the trash the morning after on my way to work. This is just wow, how do you even get to that point?
both of my parents are hoarders so i know from experience what hoarding behaviour looks like. but this is a whole new level. you need an entirely separate diagnosis for this.

Hoarders make me sad because my mom has tendencies but isn't a full on hoarder. Lots of immigrants did not have a lot growing up, so letting go of stuff as an adult is hard, even if they don't hold any value. Gotta come from a place of empathy

Hoarding is a form of OCD that runs in my family. Objects become directly related to you as a person so the more stuff you have, the more you are as a person. That's why throwing stuff away can be so traumatizing for people in this extreme condition. You're not throwing away objects - your throwing away "me."

This is just super sad. She has obviously been through trauma or something else for her to end up like this. It must be some sort of psychological coping mechanism. I can't imagine anyone living like this and being happy or healthy

Watching TLC with ken and pewds is like entertainment at its peak. 
Keep this videos coming man TLC has alot of content
As a person who LOVES to throw away things, this is just mindblowing.

This is really sad and I do wonder what happened in her life for her to lose control like this. Maybe it's also the reason why she never finished her law degree? Something traumatic could have happened around that time. If your surroundings are this disorderly, they usually reflect what is going on on the inside of you.

I wish her all the best
I love the idea of the cameraman not even wearing a safety suit or anything. Just tanking the germs, smells and rat butt bites.

It’s sad seeing people live like this, it’s clear their not well I hope she gets the help she needs

Hoarding is a very serious mental illness and people seem to think it's so funny until they are get involved or are related to someone suffering. It isn't something that can be entirely fixed with cleaning

i grew up in a hoarder home and now that i moved out i now know what a clean house is like and im also a minimalist, i dont like anything on my floors besides a rug and i just wanna keep my space clean and not end up like my dads house

edit: btw if a house gets that bad it needs to be condemned where it has to be demolished, im surprised it even got bought

Just worked a job where we were cleaning out a hoarder house that had partially burned down, spending time shoveling garbage, hoarder items, asbestos/other flame retardant materials, and ash soot etc was one of the most hazardous things I've ever done. Switched my mask like 4 times during the job, they were black but not too bad, then I realized the slight opening at the top was pitch black, prob took a year off my life for 24$/hr
Lol I love that you’re choosing to involve your son in your content Felix. Hope this channel never dies

I have family members who hoard... and it's something I battle myself daily... It's hard to explain, you just end up emotionally attached to things, or try to convince yourself that you may need them someday. I'll never be neat and tidy, much less an epic minimalist, but at least where I live will never become the sort of spectacle you see on these shows. I really need to let go of old clothes and books, though. Those are the hardest for me.
